ear, or the mini-bosses in Hate.  Does my clustering cadre of heroes in the safe camp clearing our way through constitue holding the spawn?  Implying my presence gives my hunting party first crack.  Then there is always the factor of getting attacked by the mob before someone actually hunting it has a chance to aggro it, I've often heard for KS concerns that if you aggro'ed the mob first then GM's will favor your right to the mob.  As for answering camp checks, that's a courtesy, but should never be expected.  Shouting out to the zone periodically has been said to lend creedence to one's claim when contesting a spawn. But, we've all been in the position too often fighting and missing that periodic camp check in the battle spam.  I've always felt that if you didn't respond to my camp check, and my group has started in, then we are going to share it, I'll move on, or let the god's decide our contention. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uesmalyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Esmalyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(7/23/01 7:18:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What gives your right to a spawn?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> As far as I know, the only thing that really matters is if you are &quot;the first one to engage the mob with an adequate force to kill it&quot;.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
